title: Blow at High Dough
text: "Blow at High Dough" is a song by Canadian rock band <a href="The%20Tragically%20Hip">The Tragically Hip</a>, released in April 1989 as the lead single from their first full-length studio album, "<a href="Up%20to%20Here">Up to Here</a>". It reached on the "<a href="RPM%20%28magazine%29">RPM</a>" <a href="Canadian%20content">CANCON</a> chart, and was the opening theme song of the <a href="CBC%20Television">CBC Television</a> series "<a href="Made%20in%20Canada%20%28TV%20series%29">Made in Canada</a>".
